## Limitations

The analysis is based on available literature and may not capture all nuances of the issue. The complexity of income inequality means that multiple factors interact in ways that are not fully understood. Additionally, the data and perspectives are primarily from U.S.-based sources, which may not account for global influences comprehensively. Further research could provide more insights into the interplay of these factors and their long-term implications.

